      "theory": "Ratio of short-term (12-period) to long-term (96-period) realized volatility captures regime TRANSITIONS, not just volatility levels. When the ratio spikes above 1, volatility is expanding (trending regime). When it drops below 1, volatility is contracting (mean-reverting regime). This is a term-structure signal orthogonal to single-window vol features like ATR.",
